<TITLE> Court hears charge framing against Hasina in MiG-29 case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 02 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Monday started hearing on charge framing against detained former prime minister Sheikh Hasina in the MiG-29 graft case. The prosecution lawyers presented their arguments and evidence in the court substantiating the charges. The defence lawyers will take part at the hearing on June 11. The hearing was conducted in a special court room set up in the Jatiya Sangsad complex in the presence of Judge Golam Mortuza Majumdar of Dhaka Divisional Special Judge's Court. Government prosecutor ABM Sharfuddin Khan Mukul took part at the hearing at around 10:30 am and presented his prosecution arguments against the accused till 12:15 pm. The lawyer of former army chief Gen (retd) Mustafizur Rahman, another accused in the case has appealed to the court for granting permanent bail in favour of his client and sending him abroad for treatment. The court hasn't issued any order in this regard. Hasina was produced in the court at 9:55 am. Other accused in the case are also present in the court. The now defunct Bureau of Anticorruption filed the case with Tejgaon Police Station in 2001 against seven people. Hasina, during her term as prime minister caused the state Tk 700 crore in losses by purchasing eight MiG-29 war planes, according to case details. The charge sheet was submitted on Jan 29, 2003 against Hasina and others. The High Court stayed the case proceedings following Hasina's appeal the same year. The other accused in the case are former air chief Jamaluddin Ahmed, former defence secretary Syed Yusuf Hossain, former joint secretary of the defence ministry Mohammad Hossain Sherniyabat, retd air commodore Mirza Akhter Maruf and Unique Group proprietor Noor Ali. bdnews24.
